Alissa DeRouchie <lissi0@...> wrote:

OK so this is pretty amazing.

My husband and I have been in the process of starting a new business
here in Columbus, Ohio. About a month ago I came across the website
for Intuit (the makers of Quickbooks and Quicken) and found that they
were having a contest to encourage people to start small businesses,
with a prize of $40,000 in cash and $10,000 in products and services
to get the project off the ground. To enter you had to send in a 2
minute video pitching your idea for a startup business. The deadline
was only three days away, but we got to work and sent in our video.

Our video was one of 2000, so after sending it in, we didn't think
much about it. Last Friday they called to let me know we had made it
to the final 20. I had to answer a few more questions. Today the BIG
call came in, we made it to the final 5! The finalists are now listed
on their website where the public can vote for the winner.

This is where we need help. The winner will be whoever gets the most
votes. We need your help spreading the word, and of course voting for us!

Go to this site and vote for aderouch
http://jumpup.intuit.com/start/?p=finalistVideos

You are allowed to vote once per day so keep coming back and voting
for us. Use the bookmark feature! After you create your account the
first time you will be able to come back every day and cast your vote.

We are very excited about this opportunity and would love to have your
support. Let me know what you think of our video!

Alissa DeRouchie
